about.summary: Define parameter spaces, constraints and dependencies for arbitrary algorithms, to program on such spaces. Also includes statistical designs and random samplers. Objects are implemented as 'R6' classes.

Define parameter spaces, constraints and dependencies for arbitrary algorithms, to program on such spaces. Also includes statistical designs and random samplers. Objects are implemented as 'R6' classes.

name: r-paradox
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.9.0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-paradox
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/paradox_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/paradox/paradox_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: bc418584f40ed4d08ed71207268e16488de0b5fad7d235877c74ba01522af83b

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-r6
    - r-backports
    - r-checkmate
    - r-data.table
    - r-mlr3misc >=0.5.0
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-r6
    - r-backports
    - r-checkmate
    - r-data.table
    - r-mlr3misc >=0.5.0

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('paradox')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('paradox')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://paradox.mlr-org.com, https://github.com/mlr-org/paradox
  license: LGPL-3.0-only
  summary: Define parameter spaces, constraints and dependencies for arbitrary algorithms, to program on such spaces. Also includes statistical designs and random samplers. Objects are implemented as 'R6' classes.
  license_family: LGPL
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/LGPL-3

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - pascal-git
